How many homeless are real vets and how many fakes?  Come to New York and help out in a shelter, you will see people as young as 25 and as old as 70 claiming to be Nam vets.  From my own experience, I believe that percentage to be excesive.  Anyone can claim vet status, how many really are?  Not as many as everyone thinks.<br><br>
In regards to the info Cook has provided, it was just quoted by Westmoreland and Nixon.  Each of those comes from very credible sources, many of which I have read and can post here (the sources include the Harris Poll, Gallup Poll, Dept of Defense, Federal Practioner, American Journal of Psychiatry, Combat Area Casualty File, Dept of Labor, Center for Disease Control, Veterans Adminstration. Journal of Sociology etc.)  If they are shocking, it is because Americans have been conditioned to see Nam vets as hopeless losers, and in many cases that is not so.  Until other studies are done that disprove the new numbers, facts etc, the rest is just speculation, opinion, PERSONAL VIEW etc.  
